<div id="redesign_right_column_twocolumn">


    <h1>Faculty & Gould School of Law in the News</h1>
    <p>USC Gould professors are frequently sought by the media to serve as legal experts. This section highlights news citations in which USC Gould faculty are quoted and USC Gould is featured in stories.</p>



    <ul class="itemlist">
    
        
        <li class="clearfix" style="padding-bottom: 20px; border-bottom: 1px #e3e3e3 solid;">
        
            <a href="/faculty/contactinfo.cfm?detailid=211"><img src="/portal/directory/photos100x100/sestrich.jpg" width="100" height="100" alt="Susan Estrich" class="fleft" /></a>
        
            <div class="descr">
                <h2 style="color: #000000;">The Examiner</h2>
                <h3>June 30, 2010</h3>
                <p><strong>Re: <a href="/faculty/contactinfo.cfm?detailid=211">Susan Estrich</a></strong></p>
                <p>An piece ran in response to an op-ed written by Prof. Susan Estrich of the USC Gould School about the relative inexperience of some of this year's general election contenders.
</p>
            </div>
        </li>
        
    
        
        <li class="clearfix" style="padding-bottom: 20px; border-bottom: 1px #e3e3e3 solid;">
        
            <a href="/faculty/contactinfo.cfm?detailid=68912"><img src="/portal/directory/photos100x100/edward-kleinbard-021215.jpg" width="100" height="100" alt="Edward Kleinbard" class="fleft" /></a>
        
            <div class="descr">
                <h2 style="color: #000000;">CNN</h2>
                <h3>June 29, 2010</h3>
                <p><strong>Re: <a href="/faculty/contactinfo.cfm?detailid=68912">Edward Kleinbard</a></strong></p>
                <p>Prof. Edward Kleinbard was interviewed about capping tax expenditures to reduce the federal deficit. The government does without roughly a trillion dollars a year because of tax breaks -- everything from the mortgage-interest deduction, to education and child credits, to low rates on investments. Those breaks can translate into higher tax rates and a federal budget that is much bigger than advertised, according to Kleinbard.</p>
            </div>
        </li>
        
    
        
        <li class="clearfix" style="padding-bottom: 20px; border-bottom: 1px #e3e3e3 solid;">
        
            <a href="/faculty/contactinfo.cfm?detailid=209"><img src="/portal/directory/photos100x100/Cruz_D.jpg" width="100" height="100" alt="David B. Cruz" class="fleft" /></a>
        
            <div class="descr">
                <h2 style="color: #000000;">Fox News</h2>
                <h3>June 28, 2010</h3>
                <p><strong>Re: <a href="/faculty/contactinfo.cfm?detailid=209">David B. Cruz</a></strong></p>
                <p>Prof. David Cruz served as a commentator on Fox News. He discussed the Elena Kagan hearing, and the Supreme Courts ruling on McDonald v. Chicago, a gun rights case. 
</p>
            </div>
        </li>
        
    
        
        <li class="clearfix" style="padding-bottom: 20px; border-bottom: 1px #e3e3e3 solid;">
        
            <a href="/faculty/contactinfo.cfm?detailid=399"><img src="/portal/directory/photos100x100/Roithmayr2014LR.jpg" width="100" height="100" alt="Daria Roithmayr" class="fleft" /></a>
        
            <div class="descr">
                <h2 style="color: #000000;">U.S. News and World Report</h2>
                <h3>June 28, 2010</h3>
                <p><strong>Re: <a href="/faculty/contactinfo.cfm?detailid=399">Daria Roithmayr</a></strong></p>
                <p>Prof. Daria Roithmayr was interviewed about  Elena Kagans confirmation hearing to replace retiring Justice John Paul Stevens. She will likely have to address a 1995 review she wrote of Stephen Carter's book The Confirmation Messmany court watchers concur with the thrust of her thesis. "There's very little incentive for the nominee to say anything more than what is needed to pass the confirmation process," said Roithmayr. "Since the Robert Bork hearings, the task of the nominee is simply not to say anything disqualifying." </p>
            </div>
        </li>
        
    
        
        <li class="clearfix" style="padding-bottom: 20px; border-bottom: 1px #e3e3e3 solid;">
        
            <a href="/faculty/contactinfo.cfm?detailid=372"><img src="/portal/directory/photos100x100/Stone_C.jpg" width="100" height="100" alt="Christopher D. Stone" class="fleft" /></a>
        
            <div class="descr">
                <h2 style="color: #000000;">Toledo Blade</h2>
                <h3>June 28, 2010</h3>
                <p><strong>Re: <a href="/faculty/contactinfo.cfm?detailid=372">Christopher D. Stone</a></strong></p>
                <p>An op-ed written by Prof. Christopher Stone was cited about the idea of animals suing in their own names, with human lawyers as their guardians. A more sensible way to protect the salmon, suggested University of Southern California law professor Christopher Stone in a piece he wrote recently for the Washington Post, would be to impose limits on the catches of fishermen, human beings who can understand such things, rather than on sea lions, which presumably cannot read federal regulations and thus are led only by their noses, according to the piece.</p>
            </div>
        </li>
        
    
        
        <li class="clearfix" style="padding-bottom: 20px; border-bottom: 1px #e3e3e3 solid;">
        
            <a href="/faculty/contactinfo.cfm?detailid=211"><img src="/portal/directory/photos100x100/sestrich.jpg" width="100" height="100" alt="Susan Estrich" class="fleft" /></a>
        
            <div class="descr">
                <h2 style="color: #000000;">North County Times</h2>
                <h3>June 28, 2010</h3>
                <p><strong>Re: <a href="/faculty/contactinfo.cfm?detailid=211">Susan Estrich</a></strong></p>
                <p>An op-ed by Prof. Susan Estrich ran about the increasing number of doctors who won't take new Medicare patients. "I remember the days when the health insurance industry used to advertise that Hillary Clinton would take your doctor away. She didn't," Estrich wrote. "But a lot of people have lost their doctors anyway because of the PPO rules, and lately, because doctors just don't want to put up with the rates Medicare pays."
</p>
            </div>
        </li>
        
    
        
        <li class="clearfix" style="padding-bottom: 20px; border-bottom: 1px #e3e3e3 solid;">
        
            <a href="/faculty/contactinfo.cfm?detailid=236"><img src="/portal/directory/photos100x100/Matsusaka_John.jpg" width="100" height="100" alt="John Matsusaka" class="fleft" /></a>
        
            <div class="descr">
                <h2 style="color: #000000;">KQED</h2>
                <h3>June 28, 2010</h3>
                <p><strong>Re: <a href="/faculty/contactinfo.cfm?detailid=236">John Matsusaka</a></strong></p>
                <p>Forum interviewed Prof. John Matsusaka, president of USC's Initiative and Referendum Institute, about the initiative process in California. </p>
            </div>
        </li>
        
    
        
        <li class="clearfix" style="padding-bottom: 20px; border-bottom: 1px #e3e3e3 solid;">
        
            <a href="/faculty/contactinfo.cfm?detailid=237"><img src="/portal/directory/photos100x100/edward.jpg" width="100" height="100" alt="Edward McCaffery" class="fleft" /></a>
        
            <div class="descr">
                <h2 style="color: #000000;">Boston Globe</h2>
                <h3>June 27, 2010</h3>
                <p><strong>Re: <a href="/faculty/contactinfo.cfm?detailid=237">Edward McCaffery</a></strong></p>
                <p>Prof. Edward McCaffery was quoted about the concept of voluntary taxes. To get bigger dollars out of it, I think you need bigger changes in consciousness, said McCaffery. That might be a two-way street. People arent going to do it more until they have more faith in government. But people arent going to have more faith in government until they feel they have more stake and agency. Perhaps eventually, We could be a different kind of society where we didnt think of government in such adversarial terms, McCaffery says. Things could snowball, youd have a virtuous cycle. But, he adds, You still have the possibility of government blowing that trust.</p>
            </div>
        </li>
        
    
        
        <li class="clearfix" style="padding-bottom: 20px; border-bottom: 1px #e3e3e3 solid;">
        
            <a href="/faculty/contactinfo.cfm?detailid=211"><img src="/portal/directory/photos100x100/sestrich.jpg" width="100" height="100" alt="Susan Estrich" class="fleft" /></a>
        
            <div class="descr">
                <h2 style="color: #000000;">Florida Times-Union</h2>
                <h3>June 2, 2010</h3>
                <p><strong>Re: <a href="/faculty/contactinfo.cfm?detailid=211">Susan Estrich</a></strong></p>
                <p>An op-ed by Prof. Susan Estrich ran about fatalities aboard a humanitarian-aid flotilla headed to the Gaza Strip, after it was intercepted by Israeli troops. "Israel did not intend to kill the activists," Estrich wrote. "The truth is that Israel sent too few commandos to do the job, not too many; that they did not expect resistance and were too few in number to deal with it without resorting to deadly force. It seems the Israeli military, which is usually a model for the world, wasn't a model this time." </p>
            </div>
        </li>
        
    
        
        <li class="clearfix" style="padding-bottom: 20px; border-bottom: 1px #e3e3e3 solid;">
        
            <a href="/faculty/contactinfo.cfm?detailid=226"><img src="/portal/directory/photos100x100/gkeating.jpg" width="100" height="100" alt="Gregory Keating" class="fleft" /></a>
        
            <div class="descr">
                <h2 style="color: #000000;">Los Angeles Daily Journal</h2>
                <h3>June 1, 2010</h3>
                <p><strong>Re: <a href="/faculty/contactinfo.cfm?detailid=226">Gregory Keating</a></strong></p>
                <p>A story quoted Prof. Gregory Keating  about a lawsuit involving two Los Angeles International Airport concessionaires. Airport retailer Hudson Group Retail sued Sheppard Mullin Richter & Hampton and a high-profile partner at the firm who once represented the company, alleging they breached their fiduciary duty by representing a competitor for concession lease deals at Los Angeles International Airport."It's a somewhat unusual but plausible case of fiduciary duty," said Keating. "It's not clear whether there is confidential financial information that would be useful."</p>
            </div>
        </li>
        
    
        
        <li class="clearfix" style="padding-bottom: 20px; border-bottom: 1px #e3e3e3 solid;">
        
            <a href="/faculty/contactinfo.cfm?detailid=211"><img src="/portal/directory/photos100x100/sestrich.jpg" width="100" height="100" alt="Susan Estrich" class="fleft" /></a>
        
            <div class="descr">
                <h2 style="color: #000000;">Portsmouth Herald</h2>
                <h3>May 25, 2010</h3>
                <p><strong>Re: <a href="/faculty/contactinfo.cfm?detailid=211">Susan Estrich</a></strong></p>
                <p>An op-ed by Prof. Susan Estrich ran about the United States-Mexico relationship. "It is American demand for illegal drugs that is the engine for the drug gangs operating in -- and destroying -- Mexico. And it is American assault rifles, bought at all the gun stores on the border, that are used in the killings," Estrich wrote. "We can argue until we are blue in the face about Mexicans crossing into our country illegally. But what about our responsibility for the guns that cross into their country?"</p>
            </div>
        </li>
        
    
        
        <li class="clearfix" style="padding-bottom: 20px; border-bottom: 1px #e3e3e3 solid;">
        
            <a href="/faculty/contactinfo.cfm?detailid=211"><img src="/portal/directory/photos100x100/sestrich.jpg" width="100" height="100" alt="Susan Estrich" class="fleft" /></a>
        
