            <div class="descr">
                <h2 style="color: #000000;">Pasadena Star-News</h2>
                <h3>May 12, 2010</h3>
                <p><strong>Re: <a href="/faculty/contactinfo.cfm?detailid=23758">Robert K. Rasmussen</a></strong></p>
                <p>Dean Robert Rasmussen was interviewed about the Pasadena Playhouse, which recently filed for bankruptcy. Rasmussen said that every bankruptcy case is different, but the Playhouse's future will hinge on whether the business can make money.   "The real question is whether there is an assumption that you can still be profitable on the part of the creditors," Rasmussen said. If not, he said, the assets of the group are sold off and creditors take what they can get.   
</p>
            </div>
