                <h2 style="color: #000000;">Los Angeles Daily News</h2>
                <h3>April 14, 2010</h3>
                <p><strong>Re: <a href="/faculty/contactinfo.cfm?detailid=68021">Rebecca Lonergan</a></strong></p>
                <p>Prof. Rebecca Lonergan was quoted about disputes between medical marijuana dispensaries and L.A. city attorneys. She said that prosecuting the case against a dispensary with several criminal violations may be a legal tactic by the city to dissuade the opening of more facilities. "This case is just one more step in a long battle between the marijuana dispensaries in the L.A. area and city attorneys, so I'm not sure that this particular case will have a necessary effect," said Lonergan. "(The city is) trying to make an example, sure. You've got hundreds of these popping up all over the county, so they're setting these up to a couple of cases as a deterrent to say `Stop this."' </p>
