                <h3>April 13, 2010</h3>
                <p><strong>Re: USC Gould School of Law</strong></p>
                <p>Prof.  Edward McCaffery was interviewed about why tax day falls on April 15. As the income tax applied to more people, the government had to issue more refunds, he said. "Pushing the deadline back gives the government more time to hold on to the money,"  McCaffery added.</p>
