                <h3>April 3, 2010</h3>
                <p><strong>Re: USC Gould School of Law</strong></p>
                <p>Prof. Elizabeth Garrett and Prof. Matthew McCubbins conducted research that found that when it comes to voting on ballot measures, the amount of knowledge voters have doesn't necessarily correlate with reasoned decisions. The researchers, who included a colleague at UC San Diego, suggested that voters should understand the issues on the ballot so they can be confident they are translating their preferences into reasoned decisions. The researchers proposed that voters be offered more information on the ballot itself, the story noted.</p>
            </div>
        </li>
        
    
        
