                <h2 style="color: #000000;">Daily Journal</h2>
                <h3>January 12, 2010</h3>
                <p><strong>Re: <a href="/faculty/contactinfo.cfm?detailid=214">Niels W. Frenzen</a></strong></p>
                <p>Prof. Niels Frenzen was quoted about an immigration case in which the Ninth U.S. Circuit Court of Appeals appointed an attorney to a Kenyan immigrant and urged a lower court to expedite his hearing to determine whether the man should be released from U.S. custody. "He 'won' before the 9th Circuit but that victory in terms of a direction to the lower does not mean he is any closer to being released from custody or having his case resolved on the merits," Frenzen said. "It's still potentially years away."</p>
            </div>
