                <p><strong>Re: <a href="/faculty/contactinfo.cfm?detailid=300">Elyn Saks</a></strong></p>
                <p>It was reported that Prof. Elyn Saks has received the $500,000 "genius grant" given by the John D. and Catherine T. MacArthur Foundation. Saks is one of 24 people who received the prestigious MacArthur fellowship. Saks was recognized for her scholarly work in mental health law and her memoir, "The Center Cannot Hold: My Journey Through Madness," which documents her struggles with schizophrenia. Saks said that the money will allow her to continue educating people about the lives of those with severe mental illness.</p>
